{"questionId":"22638721","questionHtml":"<p>The set of coefficients, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>, is randomly generated to form the quadratic function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Verify that this graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> has only one <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-intercept.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced><mfenced><mn>4</mn></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to solve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to express&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;as a perfect square&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is a perfect square&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>a graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></math> with the vertex touching the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A2</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> has only one <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-intercept&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22638721","referenceCode":"24M.3.AHL.TZ2.2b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"The set of coefficients, a=1, b=4 and c=4, is randomly generated to form the quadratic function fx=x2+4x+4. Verify that this graph of f has only one x-intercept.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots"],"mem